@subsubsection Step 3: Creating a Home Directory

Before setting up WinCVS, itself, you need to create a home directory somewhere
on your system.  The home directory is a place where WinCVS will store some
@sc{cvs} administrative information, such as @sc{cvs} passwords, servers you
login too etc.  For the purposes of this tutorial, it is assumed that you have
created the home directory named @file{C:\home}.
